# Context Routing Map ([PROJECT_NAME])

Read when: always at session start.
Skip when: never.

Purpose: which docs to load beyond the startup set, and when.

## Default
Start with only `AI_AGENT.md`, `docs/SESSION_BRIEF.md`, `docs/CONTEXT_ROUTING.md`. Pull deeper docs only on the triggers below.

## Triggers

| Doc | Load when |
|---|---|
| `docs/PROJECT_CANVAS.md` | milestone, scope, sequencing, or next action is unclear |
| `docs/ENGINEERING_PLAYBOOK.md` | commands, tests, CI, validation, or feature execution rules matter |
| `docs/TECH_STACK.md` | architecture, dependency, or integration boundary decisions |
| `docs/MASTER_TRACEABILITY_TABLE.md` | entrypoint, route, function chain, side-effect, or smoke evidence changes (Tier B/C) |
| `docs/OPS_SECURITY_RELEASE.md` | deploy, secrets, auth, logging, data handling, or release path changes |
| `CHANGELOG.md` | documenting a behavior change or checking recent history |
| `AI_CONTEXT.md` | nearby code reads are insufficient and a generated map exists |
| `docs/AI_MEMORY.md` | recurring preferences or prior lessons matter |
| `docs/QUICKSTART_5_MIN.md` | first-time setup of this project |

## Skip Rules
- Skip `CHANGELOG.md` for routine implementation unless documenting the change.
- Skip `OPS_SECURITY_RELEASE.md` for local UI or isolated test work.
- Skip `MASTER_TRACEABILITY_TABLE.md` for non-entrypoint edits in Tier A.
- Skip `TECH_STACK.md` when the task is local and architecture is already clear.

## Escalation
If more than three deeper docs seem necessary before the first edit, stop and ask whether the task is too broad or under-specified.
